application_type_full: Outline planning permission: Some matters reserved
description: The comprehensive mixed use redevelopment of the Lewisham Gateway Site, SE13 (land between Rennell Street and Lewisham Railway Station) for up to 100,000 m comprising retail (A1, A2, A3, A4 and A5), offices (B1), hotel (C1), residential (C3), education/health (D1) and leisure (D2) with parking and associated infrastructure, as well as open space and water features as follows: up to 57,000 m residential (C3)	 up to 12,000 m shops, financial & professional services (A1 & A2) up to 17,500 m offices (B1) / education (D1) up to 5,000 m leisure (D2)	 up to 4,000 m restaurants & cafs and drinking establishments (A3 & A4) up to 3,000 m hotel (C1)	 up to 1,000 m hot food takeaways (A5) 500m health (D1)	 provision of up to 500 car parking spaces  revised road alignment of (part of) Lewisham High Street, Rennell Street, Molesworth Street and Loampit Vale and works to Lewisham Road.
